 to come close to Earth at the end of March and may be similar or brighter. Of course comets are notoriously variable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-01T22:35:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDefinitely going north a bit to see the eclipse.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"munlander1","CreatedById":168560,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-01T22:57:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI gotta go about 2 hours south if I want to see\u00A0totality. Totally worth it though\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E( totality, totally funny funny ha ha)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}